===Etymology===
From 5th cen. {{L.}} {{term|oxymoron|lang=la}}, from {{AGr.}} {{term|ὀξύς||sharp|tr=oxus|sc=polytonic}} + {{term|μωρός||dull|tr=mōros|sc=polytonic}} [http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/cgi-bin/ptext?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0057%3Aentry%3D%2374333]. {{Gr.}} {{term|ὀξύμωρον||tr=oxumōron|sc=polytonic}} is not found in the extant Greek sources, according to the OED [http://dictionary.oed.com.ezproxy.sfpl.org/cgi/entry/50168789].

